-- A deep list built by an UNANNOTATED (dict-carrying) builder, then `++`-appended.
-- What this actually exercises, verified in the emitted IR (WASM-TMC-GAP-DESIGN.md §1):
--   1. `upto` has NO signature ⇒ it generalizes to a constrained scheme (`>` ⇒ Ord,
--      `+` ⇒ Num) ⇒ dictPass prepends a `$dict` param on the shipping path.  TMC must
--      fire on it anyway (F2(b) shape (a)) or the build recurses one frame per cell.
--   2. `++` reaches the ITERATIVE `$mdk_append` intrinsic directly (`binopBuiltinHead`
--      excludes List from the Semigroup dispatch seam) — `$mdk_append` was never the
--      recursive culprit here; a previous header claimed it was, and that false
--      diagnosis propagated into test/engine_divergence.txt and TRMC-DESIGN.md §F2(b).
-- Prints 100000 in O(1) stack.  (`++` must stay VALUE-IDENTICAL: same elements, order.)
-- EXPECT-TMC: upto
upto lo hi = if lo > hi then [] else lo :: upto (lo + 1) hi

lenAcc acc xs = match xs
  [] => acc
  _ :: t => lenAcc (acc + 1) t

main = lenAcc 0 (upto 1 50000 ++ upto 1 50000)
